Synopsis:
An ex-Navy SEAL, Michael Adams, (Matthew Reese) was captured 
during a raid to free Japanese prisoners from a North Korean 
prison camp. He endures the North Koreans torture for three 
years  seen only as flashbacks  then released back 
into civilian life.
